(1, 'Stock Market Prediction Project Using Machine Learning ', 'Stock Market Prediction System Using Machine LearningStock Market Prediction System Using Machine LearningStock Market Prediction System Using Machine LearningStock Market Prediction System Using Machine LearningStock Market Prediction System Using Machine Learning', 'Stock Market Prediction Using Machine Learning project, Stock Market Prediction Using Machine Learning Project Code, Stock Market Prediction Using Python Source Code, stock, Machine Learning Project, Machine Learning', 'stock-market-prediction-project-using-machine-learning', 1, '<p>\r\n  Welcome to the Stock Price Prediction project repository! This project\r\n  utilizes machine learning techniques to predict stock prices based on\r\n  historical data. Predicting stock prices is a challenging task, and this\r\n  project aims to explore different machine learning models to forecast future\r\n  stock prices.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Understanding Machine Learning in Finance</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nMachine learning algorithms, a subset of artificial intelligence, are designed to analyze patterns, learn from data, and make predictions. In the context of finance, these algorithms can be applied to historical stock market data to identify trends and patterns that may repeat in the future.\r\nPython: The Language of Financial Data Science<p/>\r\n<p>Python has become the language of choice for implementing machine learning models in finance. Its rich ecosystem of libraries, including NumPy, Pandas, and Scikit-learn, provides the necessary tools for data manipulation, analysis, and model development.\r\nKey Steps in Stock Market Prediction\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Features:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Data Collection:</strong> Gathered historical stock price data from\r\n    reliable sources to build a comprehensive dataset.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):</strong> Conducted thorough\r\n    analysis to understand patterns, trends, and relationships within the stock\r\n    data.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Feature Engineering:</strong> Extracted relevant features and\r\n    engineered new ones to improve the model\'s predictive performance.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Machine Learning Models:</strong> Implemented and compared various\r\n    machine learning models, including but not limited to LSTM (Long Short-Term\r\n    Memory) networks, to predict stock prices.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Evaluation Metrics:</strong> Utilized appropriate metrics to\r\n    evaluate and compare the performance of the models.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Visualization:</strong> Created insightful visualizations to better\r\n    understand the predictions and model performance.\r\n  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Technologies Used:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Python</li>\r\n  <li>TensorFlow</li>\r\n  <li>yfinance</li>\r\n  <li>Scikit-Learn</li>\r\n  <li>Pandas</li>\r\n  <li>Matplotlib</li>\r\n  <li>Jupyter Notebooks</li>\r\n  <li>Streamlit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Getting Started:</h3>\r\n<p>Go to the project directory</p>\r\n<pre>cd stock-price-prediction</pre>\r\n<p>Start the server</p>\r\n<pre>streamlit run stockmarketpredicition.py</pre>', 'stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning.png', 'stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning_1.png', 'stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning_2.png', 'stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning_3.png', 'stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning_4.png', 'r3WRDap_f4M', '100', 2, 'Machine Learning/stock-market-prediction-using-machine-learning.zip', '2024-01-10 20:07:39', '4', '473', 488),
